This paper is about a shared task on inter-personal relationship extraction, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the study of computational aspects of natural language and the design of algorithms for processing natural language data. 

The paper also mentions the various methods adopted by the participating teams, which include deep learning, feature engineering, and ensemble methods. These methods are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the evaluation methodology used during the shared task, which involves precision, recall, and F1-score. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with the representation, storage, and retrieval of information. 

Finally, the paper presents the evaluation results, which indicate the performance of the participating teams. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), which deals with the study of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
